# Shared UI vs Feature Folder Placement

- Put code in `components/ui` only when the pattern is reusable, presentational, and likely needed across multiple screens.
- Keep code in feature folders when it is domain-specific, screen-specific, or depends on feature-only logic and naming.
- Prefer composing existing shared primitives over creating a new base component.
- Do not move one-off feature markup into `components/ui` just to make it look reusable.
- If reuse is uncertain, keep the component local first and promote it later when duplication is real.
